<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: RANCHO SANTA FE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol on Wednesday was still investigating a motorcycle 
accident in which a Rancho Santa Fe man was killed when his bike hit a fence 
post. 
</P>
<P>
Timothy House, 23, of the 14000 block of Via de la Valle, was going about 50 
m.p.h. as he rounded a corner, heading west on San Dieguito Road, west of Calle 
del Nido, when he crashed about 6:15 p.m. Tuesday, authorities said. He was not 
wearing a helmet. 
</P>
<P>
"We know what happened, but we don't know why," said CHP spokesman Jerry 
Bohrer. 
</P>
<P>
House was taken to Scripps Memorial Hospital, where he died of head injuries 
shortly after 7 p.m., hospital spokesman Mike Dabney said. 
</P>
<P>
House had been working as a grounds maintenance man for the Rancho Santa Fe 
Polo Club and was test-riding a friend's motorcycle after work, a spokeswoman 
for the club said. 
</P>
