<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN PROMOTED TO OVERSEE PARK PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jackie Tatum, a 33-year veteran of the Los Angeles Recreation and Parks 
Department, has been named assistant general manager of the Valley Region, 
making her the highest-ranking black woman in the department. 
</P>
<P>
James E. Hadaway, general manager of the department, appointed Tatum to the 
$70,490-a-year post on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Tatum, 55, of Los Angeles, will oversee programs at 42 San Fernando Valley 
recreation facilities, 16 swimming pools, eight senior citizen centers, four 
18-hole golf courses, and the Hansen Dam and Sepulveda Dam recreation areas. 
</P>
<P>
A graduate of USC, Tatum joined the department in 1955 as a recreation center 
director. She succeeds Dave Gonzalez, who was appointed assistant general 
manager of the Metropolitan Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
