<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A brother and sister of Los Angeles-born sculptor Isamu Noguchi, who died Dec. 
30 at of 84, and a friend in Tokyo will share part of his estimated $5-million 
estate. Noguchi's 16-page will named his brother, Nuchio Noguchi, and friend, 
Kyoko Kawamura, as beneficiaries of 20 million yen ($160,000) each. A sister, 
Alies Spinden of Santa Fe, N.M., was left $200,000 in cash. All of his art and 
literary work, personal papers and manuscripts and the bulk of his estate will 
go to the Isamu Noguchi Foundation Inc. in New York. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
