<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 50th anniversary of American Ballet Theatre (founded in 1940) will be 
celebrated with an 18-month season and a number of special events, artistic 
director Mikhail Baryshnikov said Wednesday in New York. The plans include a 
retrospective of company repertory along with extended U.S. and international 
touring, a traveling exhibition of company memorabilia, a new PBS "Dance in 
America" telecast and a gala performance in New York next January. The company 
also has a new logo: a fuzzy blue ballerina trailing red and white veils. 
Philip Morris Companies Inc. is sponsoring the celebration and national tour 
with a grant of $750,000.ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
