<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: PICO RIVERA; 
</P>
<P>
HEARING WILL EXPLORE USES OF FEDERAL FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Community Advisory Board will hold a hearing Tuesday to receive public 
comment on how about $850,000 in federal funds should be spent in Pico Rivera. 
</P>
<P>
For the last 13 years, the federal government has given Pico Rivera Community 
Development Block Grants. The money has been used for rehabilitation of homes 
and commercial buildings, code enforcement, alley improvements, parks and the 
Senior Citizen/Art Center now under construction. 
</P>
<P>
Projects eligible for funding must either provide benefits to low- or 
moderate-income people or to eliminate slum or help improve blighted 
conditions. The hearing will begin at 7 p.m. at the Recreation and Community 
Services Building, 6767 S. Passons Blvd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
