<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: DOWNEY; 
</P>
<P>
4% HIKE IN RESIDENTIAL WATER RATES APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Downey City Council voted Tuesday to raise water rates 4% to pay for the 
increased cost of operating the municipal water system. 
</P>
<P>
The water bill for an average residential customer will jump from $23.93 for a 
two-month period to $24.96 beginning Feb. 1, Water Supt. Greg Mayfield said. 
</P>
<P>
"It's kind of like a cost-of-living increase," Mayfield said. "It's to maintain 
the current level of services." 
</P>
<P>
The Downey water system serves about 23,000 residences and businesses 
throughout the city. Water rates were last raised in January, 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
