<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LONG BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
DEVELOPMENT DIRECTOR TAKES JOB IN FREMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roger C. Anderman, director of community development in Long Beach for 2 1/2 
years, will leave his post at the end of the month to become assistant city 
manager in Fremont, a San Francisco Bay Area community of about 165,000. 
Anderman was deputy city manager in Salinas before joining the Long Beach 
Community Development Department as assistant director. 
</P>
<P>
Anderman, 44, says he counts among his achievements the creation of a low- and 
moderate-income housing fund, revival of west Long Beach redevelopment 
projects, the continued redevelopment of downtown, and progress in establishing 
an auto mall in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
