<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: RENTERS REACHING FOR 'ABOVE THE LAW' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steven Seagal was definitely the action/adventure find of 1988. His "Above the 
Law" continues to be a strong rental -- No. 5 on the Billboard magazine chart. 
Few expected it to be this high on the chart or to have such longevity (nine 
weeks on the chart). Seagal is a challenger for the No. 2 spot -- battling 
Stallone and Chuck Norris -- behind action/adventure king Arnold 
Schwarzenegger. "Bloodsport," a bloody martial arts flick starring Jean Claude 
Van Damme, is making a big splash on the rental chart (No. 17 after two weeks). 
</P>
<P>
* "Red Heat," debuting at an impressive No. 11, should be the red-hot rental of 
the next few weeks. This one wasn't great box-office, but many of those 
Schwarzenegger fans who missed it in the theaters will probably rent it. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
