<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The pilot killed in the crash of a light plane in fog on Pleasanton Ridge 
earlier in the week was identified as Barbara S. Gellman, 43, a Newport Beach 
attorney and businesswoman. Authorities said Gellman, the mother of three, was 
en route to Oakland from John Wayne Airport in Orange County for a business 
meeting when her plane crashed at about the 1,000-foot level of the ridge. The 
Federal Aviation Administration said she had radioed air traffic controllers 
for assistance as she was approaching Oakland. Controllers three times radioed 
warnings that she was flying too low in the poor visibility. Investigators said 
she acknowledged one warning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
