<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
MURDER SUSPECT FACES MENTAL TESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A judge has appointed a psychiatrist to determine the mental competency of the 
man charged with fatally shooting two Universal Studios security guards, saying 
he believed they were Nazis. 
</P>
<P>
Superior Court Judge Florence Bernstein ordered the psychiatrist to prepare his 
report on the defendant, Nathan Trupp, for a Feb. 7 hearing. 
</P>
<P>
If found to be mentally unable to understand the nature of the legal 
proceedings, Trupp will be placed in a state mental hospital until he is found 
competent to stand trial. 
</P>
<P>
Trupp is also accused of shooting to death three people in Albuquerque, N.M., 
days before the Dec. 1 shootings in Universal City. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors said Trupp shot the two security guards while stalking actor 
Michael Landon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
