<P>
Eastern Airlines, seeking to raise cash, has sold six A-300 wide-body jets to 
sister carrier Continental Airlines, the company announced. Eastern will 
receive $103 million in cash and a $67-million note at 17.5% interest for the 
sale, Eastern spokeswoman Karen Ceremsak said in Miami. The planes had been 
leased earlier to Continental and therefore will have no effect on the size of 
Eastern's fleet, she said. Ceremsak said the sale was unconnected to the 
breakdown Monday of federally mediated talks between Eastern and its machinists 
union. 
