</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ford Motor Co. fired the first round in what could be a new auto incentives 
war, announcing that it was offering 4.9% financing programs on four small car 
and truck models as well as rebates of up to $3,000 for some 1988 model cars. 
Analysts said the action reflects growing buyer concern about rising interest 
rates and could trigger other cut-rate financing programs. Ford said it is 
offering the 4.9% rate on 24-month loans on its 1989 Ford Escort and Festiva 
small cars, Mercury Tracer subcompact and the Ford Ranger small truck. It is 
offering a 3.9% financing rate on Tracer models sold in California. 
</P>
