ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
ASTHMATIC JAIL INMATE WHO DIED IS IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Orange County Jail inmate who died at UCI Medical Center in Orange was 
identified as a Santa Ana resident, Sheriff's Department officials said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Anniele Gillian, 37, had been arrested by Santa Ana police on Jan. 4 on 
suspicion of possession of narcotics. She was taken to UCI Medical Center in 
Orange Monday night after she experienced difficulty breathing, Sheriff's Lt. 
Richard J. Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
When Gillian was booked into the jail, a physician determined that she had 
acute asthma and placed her in the jail's infirmary for observation. 
</P>
<P>
Gillian began having difficulty breathing and the medical staff gave her 
medication, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
However, she suffered another asthma attack about 10:45 p.m. and the jail 
physician ordered her sent to UCI Medical Center for further evaluation and 
treatment, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
She arrived at the medical center's trauma room at 12:20 a.m. Tuesday and died 
less than 2 hours later, he said. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation is under way, and an autopsy is pending. 
</P>
</TEXT>
