<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CORONA DEL MAR BEATS THE WIND AND UNIVERSITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Smith scored midway through the second half to give Corona del Mar High 
School a 2-1 victory over University Wednesday in a Sea View League boys' 
soccer match played at Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Smith got the ball on a breakaway, beat the goalie and the wind and kicked into 
an open net. 
</P>
<P>
"He kicked it after he beat the goalie at the edge of the penalty box, and the 
wind was so fierce that the kick barely trickled in," Corona del Mar Coach John 
Connelly said. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Brown scored first for Corona del Mar (6-3-4, 1-0) in the first half. 
University tied the score, 1-1, before halftime. 
