<P>
SANTA MONICA ARMORED CAR HELD UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An armored car guard was held up shortly before 11 this morning outside a Bank 
of America near the Santa Monica Place Mall, Santa Monica police said. The 
robbers were believed to have fled, with an unknown amount of money, in a 1984 
Chevrolet, possibly a white Monte Carlo. 
</P>
<P>
An ambulance was summoned because someone was reportedly Maced during the 
robbery at 1301 Fourth St., police said. It was not known if the incident was 
connected with a series of more than a dozen armored car guard holdups during 
the last year. 
</P>
