<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCENROE, LENDL SCORE VICTORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ADELAIDE, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American John McEnroe and world-ranked No. 2 player Ivan Lendl scored 
straight-set victories today in the Rio International tennis challenge. 
</P>
<P>
McEnroe, ranked 11th in the world, upset No. 1 Mats Wilander of Sweden 6-4, 6-3 
at the Memorial Drive courts. Lendl scored a 6-4, 7-6 triumph over Australian 
Mark Woodeforde. 
</P>
<P>
The event, a six-man round-robin exhibition, is a warm-up for the Australian 
Open, which starts Monday at Melbourne. 
</P>
<P>
McEnroe had lost in straight sets to Australian Pat Cash in his first match 
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
