<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BODY BUILDERS TO BE DRUG-TESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manitoba will become the first Canadian province to impose mandatory drug 
testing on amateur body builders, at the provincial championships in June, the 
president of the Manitoba Amateur Body Building Assn. said. 
</P>
<P>
Randy Pearson said it's time to start weeding out steroid users. 
</P>
<P>
"They are taking the place of people who don't use steroids by winning at a 
lower level and then not being able to compete after that, because there is 
testing on national and international levels," Pearson said. 
</P>
<P>
He said he didn't expect the plan to meet much resistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
