<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a chart on the highest-paid U.S. executives in 1987, Charles Lazarus, 
chairman of Toys R Us, was inadvertently omitted from the list. Lazarus, who 
earned $60 million for the year, should have been listed first. 
</P>
</TEXT>
